        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(minimax): bound JSON response reads to prevent OOM",
        "body": "## What Problem This Solves\n\nReplace unbounded `await response.json()` with `readResponseWithLimit` (1 MiB cap)\nacross MiniMax oauth/video-generation paths, preventing OOM from oversized upstream HTTP responses.\n\n## Changes\n\n| File | Change |\n|------|--------|\n| `extensions/minimax/oauth.ts` | 1 MiB cap for token endpoint JSON |\n| `extensions/minimax/video-generation-provider.ts` | 1 MiB cap for poll/metadata/create JSON (download paths already bounded) |\n\n## Evidence\n\n### Real HTTP bounded-read proof\n\n```\nnode --import tsx test/_proof_minimax_bound.mts\n\n[proof] real server on :58033, cap=1048576 bytes, would-stream≈67108864 bytes\n\nPASS  oversized body: throws bounded cap error :: threw=true\nPASS  stream cancelled at cap: server sent ≈ cap bytes, not ~64 MiB :: bytesSent=1048576\nPASS  happy path: small JSON parsed correctly :: status=ok id=batch-1\nPASS  negative control: unbounded read buffers PAST cap :: buffered=33554457 bytes (> 1048576)\n\n[proof] 4 PASS, 0 FAIL\n```\n\n### MiniMax extension unit tests\n\n```\npnpm exec vitest run extensions/minimax/\n\n Test Files  10 passed | 1 failed (11)\n      Tests  134 passed | 2 failed (136)\n   Duration  102.60s\n```\n\nThe 2 failures are Windows `EBUSY` file-lock errors on temp SQLite files,\nunrelated to the bounded JSON changes.\n\n_AI-assisted._",
